Jenna Etheridge, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A woman in the front seat of a minibus-taxi was the sole survivor of a head-on collision with a truck outside of Middelburg, ER24 paramedics said on Sunday. The crash around 21:00 on Saturday killed 10 people in the taxi, said spokesperson Werner Vermaak.When medics arrived on Old Middelburg Road in Mpumalanga, they found the 22-year-old woman had been seriously injured.They extricated her from the vehicle and rushed her to a nearby hospital.The truck driver sustained minor injuries and was taken to the same hospital, said Vermaak.Police were on the scene to investigate the accident. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.